As the sun rises over the bustling streets of downtown, Emma makes her way to her part-time job at the local grocery store. She's been working as a cashier for three years now, and it's become a familiar routine for her. She clocks in, puts on her name tag, and gets settled behind the register.

The first customers of the day start trickling in, and Emma greets each one with a warm smile. She knows many of them by name, and they know her. There's Mrs. Johnson, who always asks about Emma's weekend;
